race.comment: MAYSOONFLY (10) made an encouraging debut last time out, finishing fourth in a handy maiden over 1100m at Morphettville. Is sure to have come on from that and can get off the mark this time. TOTAL LOVE (5) is on debut for the Matthew Seyers stable. Three-year-old gelding by Shalaa from Equal Love. Comes here off a recent trial win. One to keep tabs on, particularly if popular in betting. SETTLE PETAL (11) is a filly by Graff out of Distraught who is at the races for the first time today. Looks ready after placing in a recent Morphettville trial. Betting watch advised. MARCEL (4) didn't make an impact on debut back in August before spelling but looks to have come on a treat during the break. Gets in well with the 2kg claim and if the market support is there, he's one to definitely consider. ELEGANT LILLY (9) was good when resuming at Oakbank last month, before a flat effort second-up. Fitter third-up and can get things back on track.
